Maths

  • My supervisors are Masoud Kamgarpour, Anna Pusks and Ole Warnaar.
  • I am doing a Master of Philosophy at UQ. My topic is character varieties, focusing on the 2011 paper Arithmetic Harmonic Analysis on Character and Quiver Varieties by Hausel, Letellier and Rodriguez-Villegas. Roughly, my projects goal is to use results in Deligne-Lusztigs 1976 paper Representations of Reductive Groups Over Finite Fields to prove that the \(\mathbb{F}_q\)-points of the \(k\)-punctured genus-\(g\) representation variety \(\mathrm{Hom}(\Gamma_{g,k},G(\mathbb{F}_q))\) is a polynomial in \(q\) for a reductive group \(G\) of arbitrary type, find expressions for these polynomials in the vein of Hausel-Letellier-Rodriguez-Villegas and then relate these polynomials to the polynomials of MacDonald.
  • I have completed a Bachelor of Mathematics (Honours) at UQ. My honours thesis is titled Hecke Algebras and Gelfand Pairs in Representation Theory. Thesis topics include: Hecke algebras of finite groups, Gelfand pairs, the GelfandGraev representation, Hecke algebras of finite groups of Lie type, Hecke algebras of locally compact groups, the spherical Hecke algebra, the IwahoriHecke algebra.
